<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When filtering a string with underscore to camel case, underscores are retained if the string contains a numeric.</p>

<p>$a = 'this_has_a_24_number';
$filter = new Zend_Filter_Word_UnderscoreToCamelCase();
echo $filter-&gt;filter($a);</p>

<p>OUTPUT: ThisHasA_24Number</p>

<p>I'm not entirely sure if this is the expected behaviour or not as you obviously cannot camel case numerics. However I feel the underscore should at least be removed after being passed through the filter.</p>

